<p>I have been working on a web application that can download the files from particular directory in google drive. </p>  <p>I am uploading the content using google hosted script and it works well.</p>  <p>I am struggling with downloading those uploaded file using API. I tried different scripts but I cannot get the uploaded files.</p>  <p>Following is my downloading script</p>  <pre><code>&lt;?php require_once realpath(dirname(__FILE__).'/google-api-php-client/src/Google/autoload.php');  $client_email = 'example@developer.gserviceaccount.com'; $private_key = file_get_contents('my.p12');  $scopes = array(     'https://www.googleapis.com/auth/drive'); $credentials = new Google_Auth_AssertionCredentials(     $client_email,     $scopes,     $private_key );   $client = new Google_Client(); $client-&gt;setAssertionCredentials($credentials); if ($client-&gt;getAuth()-&gt;isAccessTokenExpired()) {   $client-&gt;getAuth()-&gt;refreshTokenWithAssertion();   }  $service = new Google_Service_Drive($client);  $optParams = array(   'maxResults' =&gt; 10, );  $results = $service-&gt;files-&gt;listFiles($optParams); echo count($results-&gt;getItems()); if (count($results-&gt;getItems()) == 0) {   print "No files found.\n"; } else {   print "Files:\n";   foreach ($results-&gt;getItems() as $file) {     $data  = downloadFile($service, $file);      $fileName = $file-&gt;getOriginalFilename();     file_put_contents($fileName, $data);     printf("%s (%s)\n", $file-&gt;getTitle(), $file-&gt;getOriginalFilename());   } }   function downloadFile($service, $file) {   $downloadUrl = $file-&gt;getDownloadUrl();    if ($downloadUrl) {     $request = new Google_Http_Request($downloadUrl, 'GET', null, null);     $httpRequest = $service-&gt;getClient()-&gt;getAuth()-&gt;authenticatedRequest($request);     if ($httpRequest-&gt;getResponseHttpCode() == 200) {       return $httpRequest-&gt;getResponseBody();     } else {       // An error occurred.         echo "An error occurred\n";       return nul